ures that utilize AI-driven insights such as sentiment analysis and audience segmentation, and contribute meaningfully to Disney's mission of delivering unforgettable guest experiences.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in AI model development, cross-platform integration, and technical communication — skills that translate directly into the collaborative culture and innovation Disney values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion for fashion design generation, leveraging CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA on Pace University's HPC cluster for AI model training, fine-tuning, and audience segmentation analysis. I deployed AI models using vLLM and Hugging Face, implementing secure model serving with RESTful API endpoints for cross-platform integration and personalized recommendations — experience that aligns directly with Disney's focus on AI-enhanced solutions that redefine personalization and optimize content recommendations. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops on GPU programming with CUDA, Mojo, and building AI Agents with LangChain, LangGraph, and LangSmith for 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly, participate actively in collaborative learning environments, and document my work thoroughly — directly mirroring the Agile team ceremonies, code reviews, and documentation responsibilities central to this role. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor, communicates with clarity, and thrives in collaborative, innovation-driven environments.

I have always been passionate about creativity, technology, and innovation that inspires optimism and delivers unforgettable experiences, and I envision myself contributing my talent to furthering Disney's mission of creating entertainment and inspiration for a global audience. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

